race.comment: STATE OF BOOM (6) is a debutant for Grant and Alana Williams with Pike in the saddle. His latest trial at Lark Hill was strong and Pike sticks from that heat. Needs some luck from the wide alley, but has some ability and can make his presence felt. SEASTIC (11) resumes today with a very impressive trial under her belt. She improved sharply at her second trial and Carbery now rides from an inside draw. Can feature if she runs up to that effort. ARCTIC SNOW (9) is another who has trialled well coming into this. Her trial was much slower than STATE OF BOOM on the same day, but she was a good winner. Can make her presence felt on resumption. EIGHTYSEVEN LAD (3) felt the pinch last start when out to 1400m. Back in trip today and an improved run is on the cards. HELIOS AMIGOS (2) wasn't far away last time out and can feature again.
